text.title: Tort Bunny (thinking)
text.tspan: Okay, Tortious. You can do this.

text.title: Tort Bunny (thinking)
text.tspan: Eye of the tiger. Eye of the--.

text.title: Evil Sammich Judge (off-panel)
text.tspan: Counsel?

text.title: Evil Sammich Judge
text.tspan: We're waiting.

text.title: Tort Bunny (off-panel)
text.tspan: Yes, your highness.
I mean, your honor.

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: Good evening.

text.title: Evil Sammich Judge (off-panel)
text.tspan: It's 10 in the morning.

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: I mean good afternoon, and
may it lead you to a horse.

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: I mean, may I please some whores!

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: No, court! Court! May it please the
tort! My name is Courteous Bunny,
and I -- Tortious! I am not courteous.

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: I mean I am courteous, except -- I'm
sorry, I'm Tortious! But my name is who
my name is what I'm trying to get across
my three points this afternoon morning
before my prima facie case is I'd like
to reserve five minutes for a Red Bull.

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: My name is Tortious Rabbit,
and may I pee in my shorts.

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: I mean Bunny! Like Chubby Bunny.

text.title: Evil Sammich Judge (off-panel)
text.tspan: Counsel, why--

text.title: Tort Bunny
text.tspan: CHUBBY BUNNY IS A FLUFFY BUNNY!
CHUBBAY BUNNAY! CHUHA BWUHAY!
Cite as: Andrew Fong, May It Please the Court, TORT BUNNIES (April 11, 2011), http://tortbunnies.com/90.html.
